      .legal-content

        .legal-section
          h2.legal-section-title 1. Acceptance of Terms
          p By accessing or using Hedge Wears (the &ldquo;Platform&rdquo;) &mdash; whether via the website, iOS app, or Android app &mdash; you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service (&ldquo;Terms&rdquo;). If you do not agree, do not use the Platform.
          p These Terms form a legally binding agreement between you and Hedge Wears. We may update these Terms from time to time. Continued use of the Platform after updates are published constitutes your acceptance of the revised Terms.
          p Hedge Wears is built on infrastructure provided by Vendorstack. By using the Platform, you acknowledge that your account and transactions are also processed by Vendorstack and that you are simultaneously a customer of Vendorstack. The Vendorstack Platform Terms apply alongside these Terms where relevant.

        .legal-section
          h2.legal-section-title 2. Account Registration
          p To purchase products or earn HedgeCoin, you must create an account. You agree to:
          ul
            li Provide accurate, current, and complete information during registration.
            li Maintain the security of your password and immediately notify us of any unauthorised access.
            li Not create accounts for others without their consent.
            li Not share your account credentials with any third party.
          p You must be at least 16 years old to create an account. By registering, you confirm that you meet this requirement.

        .legal-section
          h2.legal-section-title 3. Products &amp; Orders
          p Products listed on Hedge Wears are sold by independent sellers ("Sellers"). Hedge Wears acts as a marketplace facilitator and is not the seller of record for most transactions.
          ul
            li Sellers are responsible for the accuracy of product descriptions, images, pricing, and availability.
            li By placing an order, you make an offer to purchase from the Seller at the listed price.
            li An order is confirmed once you receive an order confirmation notification.
            li Prices are displayed in HedgeCoin (HGC) with an optional local currency equivalent for reference.
          p Hedge Wears reserves the right to cancel orders in cases of pricing errors, fraud suspicion, or payment failure.

        .legal-section
          h2.legal-section-title 4. HedgeCoin Terms
          p HedgeCoin (HGC) is Hedge Wears' loyalty currency. The following rules apply:
          ul
            li HGC is earned on completed purchases as determined by Hedge Wears from time to time.
            li HGC can be redeemed at checkout to reduce the cost of eligible orders.
            li HGC has no cash value and cannot be transferred, sold, or exchanged for fiat currency.
            li HGC does not expire while your account is active. If your account is closed or terminated, any remaining HGC balance will be forfeited.
            li Hedge Wears reserves the right to modify the HGC earning rate, redemption rate, or other programme terms at any time with reasonable notice.
            li HGC obtained through fraud, manipulation, or violation of these Terms will be forfeited and your account may be suspended.

        .legal-section
          h2.legal-section-title 5. Prohibited Conduct
          p You agree not to:
          ul
            li Use the Platform for any unlawful purpose or in violation of any applicable law or regulation.
            li Attempt to gain unauthorised access to any account, system, or network connected to Hedge Wears.
            li Post false, misleading, or fraudulent product listings, reviews, or information.
            li Circumvent, disable, or interfere with security or access controls.
            li Scrape, crawl, or systematically extract data from the Platform without our prior written consent.
            li Use the Platform to transmit spam, malware, or other malicious content.
            li Engage in any conduct that disrupts or interferes with the experience of other users.

        .legal-section
          h2.legal-section-title 6. Intellectual Property
          p All content on the Platform — including the Hedge Wears logo, design, copy, and software — is owned by or licensed to Hedge Wears and is protected by copyright and other intellectual property laws. You may not reproduce, distribute, or create derivative works without our express written permission.
          p Sellers retain ownership of their product images and descriptions, but grant Hedge Wears a non-exclusive licence to display that content on the Platform.

        .legal-section
          h2.legal-section-title 7. Limitation of Liability
          p To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, Hedge Wears shall not be liable for:
          ul
            li Any indirect, incidental, special, or consequential damages arising from your use of the Platform.
            li Loss of profits, data, or goodwill.
            li The acts or omissions of independent Sellers, including product defects, misdescription, or non-delivery.
            li Any interruption, suspension, or termination of the Platform.
          p Our total aggregate liability to you for any claim arising from these Terms or your use of the Platform shall not exceed the total amount you paid to Hedge Wears in the 12 months preceding the claim.

        .legal-section
          h2.legal-section-title 8. Governing Law
          p These Terms are governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of England and Wales. Any disputes shall be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of England and Wales.

        .legal-section
          h2.legal-section-title 9. Vendorstack Platform
          p Hedge Wears is operated on the Vendorstack commerce platform. Vendorstack provides the core infrastructure that powers our product catalogue, order processing, payments, user accounts, HedgeCoin rewards, and business management tools.
          p By registering an account or completing a purchase on Hedge Wears, you become a customer of Vendorstack as well as Hedge Wears. As a result:
          ul
            li Your account data, order history, and transaction records are stored and processed within the Vendorstack platform.
            li Vendorstack may send you transactional emails and communications related to your account, orders, platform security, and service updates.
            li Vendorstack may contact you with information relevant to the services they provide to power Hedge Wears.
            li Your use of the Platform is also subject to the Vendorstack Platform Terms and Privacy Policy, which govern how your data is processed at the infrastructure level.
          p Hedge Wears remains responsible for the brand experience, product curation, and customer service you receive. Vendorstack&rsquo;s role is to provide the technical foundation that makes the Platform operate.

        .legal-section
          h2.legal-section-title 10. Contact
          p If you have questions about these Terms, please contact us at:
          p
            a.link(href='mailto:hello@hedgewears.com') hello@hedgewears.com
          p Hedge Wears, London, United Kingdom.
